@jjhack3r 
Flyback transformers
Thank you for pointing that out. I didn't know that.

@jjhack3r half decent class D's type would look at the output voltage and use that and reference input  to determine how/when  to switch their half bridge.

doesn't need to be that complex a circuit.... 
LM339 IC etc that picks up a scaled copy of the output and compares that to what output should be at the time should easily keep output voltage to within a small % error of the scaling of the reference voltage. if powered device can't cope with such voltage errors, it probably shouldn't be plugged into real mains.
